N2  - This article begins with two statements which summarize why laboratory experiments are either sensible or senseless. The author then discusses how the laboratory can be used to think more imaginatively about organizations. He notes that the lab setting allows researchers to make use of experimental simulations that field work does not allow and that researchers can also manipulate their variables in the lab. He addresses researchers that have criticized laboratory research techniques in studying organizations by noting the lack of research on complex organizations and urging work in that field.
